{"name": "pqdm", "metadata": {"name": "pqdm", "version": "0.2.0", "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 2 - Pre-Alpha", "Intended Audience :: Developers", "License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Natural Language :: English", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.6", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.7", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.8", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.9"], "home_page": "https://github.com/niedakh/pqdm", "license": "MIT license", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["bounded-pool-executor", "tqdm", "typing-extensions"], "summary": "PQDM is a TQDM and concurrent futures wrapper to allow enjoyable paralellization of progress bars.", "upload_time": 1644833778}, "documentation": ["# Parallel TQDM\n\n```{image} https://img.shields.io/pypi/v/pqdm.svg\n:target: https://pypi.python.org/pypi/pqdm\n```\n\n```{image} https://readthedocs.org/projects/pqdm/badge/?version=latest\n:alt: Documentation Status\n:target: https://pqdm.readthedocs.io/en/latest/?badge=latest\n```\n\n```{image} https://pyup.io/repos/github/niedakh/pqdm/shield.svg\n:alt: Updates\n:target: https://pyup.io/repos/github/niedakh/pqdm/\n```\n\nPQDM is a TQDM and concurrent futures wrapper to allow enjoyable paralellization of\niterating through an Iterable with a progress bar.\n\n- Free software: MIT license\n- Documentation: <https://pqdm.readthedocs.io>.\n\n## Install & Use\n\nTo install\n\n```\npip install pqdm\n```\n\nand use\n\n```\nfrom pqdm.processes import pqdm\n# If you want threads instead:\n# from pqdm.threads import pqdm\n\nargs = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5]\n# args = range(1,6) would also work\n\ndef square(a):\n    return a*a\n\nresult = pqdm(args, square, n_jobs=2)\n```\n\nFor more examples variants check the [Usage](https://pqdm.readthedocs.io/en/latest/usage.html) section of the docs.\n\n## Features\n\n- parellize your tqdm runs using processes or threads thanks to concurrent.futures,\n- just import `pqdm` from `pqdm.threads` or `pqdm.processes` to start,\n- automatic usage of `tqdm.notebook` when iPython/Jupyter notebook environment detected, custom tqdm class accepted\n- automatic parsing of `pqdm` kwargs and separating between `concurrent.Executor` args and `tqdm` args,\n- support for any iterable and passing items as kwargs, args or directly to function which is being applied\n- support bounded exectutors via <https://github.com/mowshon/bounded_pool_executor>\n\n## Credits\n\nThis package was created with [Cookiecutter] and the [audreyr/cookiecutter-pypackage] project template.\n\n# History\n\n## 0.2.0 (2022-02-14)\n\n- Adds exception handling\n- Allows using custom tqdm_class (like tqdm_discord)\n- Minor fixes\n\n## 0.1.0 (2020-03-07)\n\n- Some updates in progress reporting and documentation.\n\n## 0.0.1 (2020-03-05)\n\n- First release on PyPI.\n\n[audreyr/cookiecutter-pypackage]: https://github.com/audreyr/cookiecutter-pypackage\n[cookiecutter]: https://github.com/audreyr/cookiecutter\n"], "modules": [{"name": "pqdm.utils", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "pqdm.utils._inside_jupyter", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": {"name": "bool", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.bool", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pqdm.utils._divide_kwargs", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "kwargs", "type": {"name": "KwArgs", "xref": {"fqname": "KwArgs", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "executor_class", "type": {"name": "Executor", "xref": {"fqname": "concurrent.futures._base.Executor", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "Tuple", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Tuple", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "KwArgs", "xref": {"fqname": "KwArgs", "project": null}, "params": null}, {"name": "KwArgs", "xref": {"fqname": "KwArgs", "project": null}, "params": null}]}, "documentation": []}], "variables": [{"name": "pqdm.utils.KwArgs", "type": null, "documentation": []}]